oai_dc:dc.dc:title: WAVE PRESSURE FORMULA FOR PERFORATED CAISSON WITH DOUBLE CHAMBERS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Oh, Sang-Ho
Ji, Chang-Hwan
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Some of perforated caisson breakwaters have double wave chambers, for which no clear guideline for estimating design load is available. The well-known Takahashi's formula (Takahashi and Shimosako, 1994) is basically applicable to single-chamber perforated caisson. Considering this, we conducted physical experiment to develop a wave pressure formula for double-chamber perforated caisson.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 36 (2018): Proceedings of 36th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Baltimore, Maryland, 2018; structures.34
